name: it was by falling that I learned how to run
description:
This is a very special photograph from my childhood. This tricycle belonged to a neighbor, then became mine, and was passed on to several other children.

Children who learned from their falls that you can't go beyond the ground.

I embroidered on it the phrase "it was by falling that I learned how to run" because we must remember that the wind has the capacity to dry our tears.So run, run as fast as you can.

dimensions: 6 cm x 8 cm
